Klever Wallet Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 09/17/2024
This Privacy Policy explains the collection, usage, disclosure, and protection of your personal information when you use our services. By accessing or utilizing our services, you accept the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy. If you disagree with any part of this policy, please refrain from using our services.
1. Data Collection
1.1 Personal Data
– No personal data is collected due to the nature of the our services. However, due to the nature of the services provided
IP addresses, operating system, device identifiers
are identified by our systems.
No data or information is saved beyond those exposed by internet traffic and access to downloads from Google Play, Apple Store, etc.
1.2 Usage Information
– Details about how you interact with our services, such as features you use and links you click, are collected solely for the purpose of improving user experience and optimizing the functionality of our platform. This information is analyzed to enhance service performance and provide a more tailored and efficient experience
2. Utilization of Your Data
We utilize the collected information for various purposes, including:
– Service Provision and Maintenance: To ensure the proper functioning, monitoring, and enhancement of our services.
– Communication: To respond to inquiries, send notifications about services, and provide updates or information related to our services.
– Service Improvement: To analyze usage for enhancing the platform, developing new features, and improving user experience.
– Marketing and Promotions: To offer and manage promotions, contests, and special offers. You can opt-out of these communications by following the unsubscribe instructions in any email we send.
3. Information Sharing
We may share your information under the following conditions:
3.1 Service Providers
– With third-party service providers who perform services on our behalf.
3.2 Business Transactions
– In connection with or during negotiations of any merger, sale of company assets, financing, or acquisition of all or a portion of our business by another company.
3.3 Legal Compliance
– To comply with legal obligations, such as court orders, subpoenas, or in response to lawful requests by public authorities, including national security or law enforcement requirements.
3.4 Affiliates
– With our affiliates, requiring them to honor this Privacy Policy. Affiliates include our parent company and subsidiaries, joint venture partners, or other companies we control or that are under common control with us.
3.5 With Your Consent
– For any other purpose with your consent.
4. Data Security
We adopt appropriate technical and organizational measures to safeguard your data from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. These measures include encryption, access controls, and secure protocols. However, no internet transmission or electronic storage method is entirely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
5. International Data Transfers
Your information may be transferred to and stored on computers located outside your state, province, country, or other governmental jurisdiction where data protection laws may differ from those of your jurisdiction. We will take all reasonably necessary steps to ensure that your data is treated securely and in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
6. Contact Information
For any questions or support for any of our products access the website:
https://support.klever.org/
For questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
– Email: privacy@klever.com
7. Your Data Protection Rights
Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal information:
To exercise these rights, contact us
at privacy@
klever.com. We will respond within a reasonable timeframe.
8. Data Retention
We retain your personal information only as long as necessary for the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, including satisfying any legal, accounting, or reporting requirements. When no longer needed, we will securely delete or anonymize your personal data. Maximo de 5 anos.
9. Children’s Privacy
Our services are not intended for people under 18.
10. External Links
Our services may include links to external websites not operated by us. If you click on a third-party link, you will be directed to that third party’s site. We recommend reviewing the Privacy Policy of each site you visit.
11. Policy Updates
We may revise this Privacy Policy periodically. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated “Effective Date” at the top. Your continued use of our services after changes are made constitutes acceptance of the new policy.
To provide the best experiences, we use technologies like cookies to store and/or access device information. Consenting to these technologies will allow us to process data such as browsing behavior or unique IDs on this site. Not consenting or withdrawing consent, may adversely affect certain features and functions.
The technical storage or access is strictly necessary for the legitimate purpose of enabling the use of a specific service explicitly requested by the subscriber or user, or for the sole purpose of carrying out the transmission of a communication over an electronic communications network.
The technical storage or access is necessary for the legitimate purpose of storing preferences that are not requested by the subscriber or user.
The technical storage or access that is used exclusively for statistical purposes.
The technical storage or access that is used exclusively for anonymous statistical purposes. Without a subpoena, voluntary compliance on the part of your Internet Service Provider, or additional records from a third party, information stored or retrieved for this purpose alone cannot usually be used to identify you.
The technical storage or access is required to create user profiles to send advertising, or to track the user on a website or across several websites for similar marketing purposes.
